374.230.  Fees — paid to director. — Every individual or entity making a filing with the department described below shall pay to the director the following fees and charges, to be paid into the insurance dedicated fund established under section 374.150:
  (1)  For filing the declaration required on organization of each domestic company, one thousand dollars;
  (2)  For filing statement and certified copy of charter required of foreign companies, one thousand dollars;
  (3)  For filing application to renew certificate of authority, along with all required annual reports, including the annual statement, actuarial statement, risk-based capital report, report of valuation of policies or other obligations of assurance, and audited financial report annual statement of any company doing business in this state, two thousand dollars;
  (4)  For filing the ORSA summary report required by sections 382.500 to 382.550, or a preacquisition notification required by sections 382.040 to* 382.060, or section 382.095, five hundred dollars;
  (5)  Unless otherwise specified in subdivision (4) or another section of law, for any filings required under chapter 382, two hundred fifty dollars;
  (6)  For filing any paper, document, or report for which a filing fee is not otherwise provided for in another section of law that is not filed under subdivision (1), (2), (3), (4), or (5), but required to be filed in the office of the director, one hundred fifty dollars each.
(RSMo 1939 §§ 5795, 5796, A.L. 1945 p. 1018, A. 1949 H.B. 2115, A.L. 1967 p. 516, A.L. 1989 S.B. 250, A.L. 2007 S.B. 66, A.L. 2018 S.B. 982) 
Prior revisions: 1929 §§ 5685, 5686; 1919 §§ 6096, 6097; 1909 §§ 6890, 6891 
Effective 1-01-19
*Word "through" appears in original rolls.
